  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strenghtening the National Response to HIV/AIDS in Guyana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The implementation of this project will contribute to the reduction in HIV prevalence among female sex workers, miners and loggers including mobile populations in the hinterland regions 1, 7, 8 and 9 by raising awareness on sexual health promotion and prevention. HIV preventative services will be extended throughout the regions to target mining and logging communities that are most at-risk and vulnerable. Through the strengthening of preventative measures such as the sharing of information and culturally appropriate activities, beneficiaries will be sensitized on the general health issues including HIV/AIDS and STIs. This is to be achieved by identifying and filling gaps in health service delivery, gathering, documenting and sharing information and best practices for meeting migrants&apos; health needs in countries of origin or return, transit and destination; raising health service providers&apos; and professionals&apos; cultural and gender sensitivity to migrants&apos; health issues; and training health professionals to deal with the health issues associated with population movements.</narrative>
  </description>
